            "question": "Where do I park?",
            "answer": "<p>Street parking is available on Willow Street and surrounding blocks. The studio is also a 5-minute walk from the Clark Street subway station (2/3 trains). Bike racks are available at the front entrance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq-2": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you offer private lessons?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes — private sessions are available with any of our instructors. Sessions can be tailored to your goals, whether that's working through an injury, deepening your practice, or learning the basics. Contact us to schedule.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq-3": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What's the best class for beginners?",
            "answer": "<p>We recommend starting with Hatha or Yin. Both are slower-paced with clear instruction and modifications for every pose. Our teachers are experienced at making newcomers feel welcome and comfortable.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq-4": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How do I cancel a booking?",
            "answer": "<p>You can cancel through your online account up to 4 hours before class. Late cancellations or no-shows will be deducted from your class pack. Unlimited members are not charged for cancellations.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
